Mauritania's EEZ is the fifth-largest target of subsidized distant-water fishing in the world. It's a challenge shared by other African countries, which are losing out to aggressive foreign fleets from big fishing nations, primarily in Europe and Asia, that have depleted fish populations in their own waters and come to Africa to fill their nets. Ernesto Fernández Monge and U. Rashid Sumaila offer hope that after more than two decades of negotiations, a solution might be within reach as WTO members' trade ministers gather in Geneva for a ministerial conference Nov. 30 through Dec. 3. Read on.